{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Topping","content":["Place sweet potatoes in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water then cook <b>12 min\/100°C\/speed 0.5<b>. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 170°C and lightly grease 2 x 6-hole doughnut tins. Drain through a sieve then return to mixing bowl.","Add oil, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla to mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add flour, baking powder, ground cinnamon, ground ginger, ground nutmeg and salt then mix <b>7 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>2 sec\/speed 4<b>. Divide between prepared doughnut holes. Bake for 20-24 minutes (170°C) until cooked and golden. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","Allow doughnuts to cool in tins for a few minutes, then loosen with a knife and carefully transfer to a wire rack. Meanwhile, make topping."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Doughnuts","content":["150 g sweet potatoes, peeled, cut in pieces","150 g water","40 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","120 g granulated sugar","200 g whole milk","1 large egg","2 tsp vanilla extract","200 g plain flour","1 ½ tsp baking powder","1 ½ tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp ground ginger","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["30 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled","4 Tbsp icing sugar","2 tsp water, boiling"]}],"id":"r143358","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-iIYXyGeXM-s\/XZWq978BMQI\/AAAAAAAAfgM\/gTi6_1W7Yws3bGsiFA3ANusOR0SLoRoJQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ZobG0W0JRuA1UzJw.png","title":"Sweet Potato Doughnuts","publishedAt":"2017-03-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.4 g","fat":"6.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"33 g","calories":"850 kJ \/ 203 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fine sieve, 2 x 6 hole doughnut tins (Ø 8 cm), wire rack, pastry brush, oven","basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","12 pieces"]}